I'll start from the end: this time it's not an April prank. This is a real thing.
The projects you will be exposed to today, are my way of hugging you back, for all the hugs you have given me over the past five years.

In recent years and especially at the beginning of my work, it was possible to think, and also hear from people, that dealing with cultivation is a superficial matter. More cream, more serum, more stupidity.
But when I began my journey with the realization that my skin carried enormous weight over my self-image, I realized that nurturing myself was an evolutionary survival act in order to feel better about myself.
Fast forward, a few years back, the first ingredient that caught my attention was "oxybenzone" and from that I understood that all my life I was taught to be careful of what is healthy or not in my diet, but they did not make me ask questions about what happens after I put on cream.

It took me time, to understand, to crack, and slowly I poured out what I had learned here with the help of these limited platforms of the cliffs and the Chinese and all this time - I was missing something. And not only me, but you too. With how much I tried to design all the highlight, arrange, call it by name, lacateg, there was a lack of order and organization.
